Peel and finely dice the @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and just bash the @garlic clove{1} and finely chop your @parsley{1}(finely chopped).

> Keep the garlic relatively whole so you can remove it once it has done its job and released its flavour.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #pan{} on medium heat. Once warm, gently cook the onion for ~{3%minutes} until soft. Strip the leaves from the @thyme{} stalks and add into the pan.

> If the onions begin to colour add 1 tbsp of water and turn the heat down a bit.

Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{2} to the onions along with the smashed garlic and cook for ~{5%minutes}.

> You want the pancetta to go ever so slightly crispy at the edges.

Add the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @muscovado sugar{1%tsp}, @chopped tomatoes{1%tin} and @mixed beans{1%tin}(drained). Add @salt{1%tsp} and a few good grinds of @pepper{}. Give it all a good stir and let it bubble gently for ~{20%minutes} or until it is nice and thick. Give it a stir every now and then and add the chopped parsley at the end of cooking.

Bring a large #pot{} of water to a gentle boil with a @salt{1%tsp}. Peel the @potato{4} and cut into approximately 3cm cubes and add to the water. Gently cook for around ~{15%minutes} until soft enough to mash (a #knife{} will slip easily through). Once drained, mash the potato with a little @?milk{} and @?butter{}(if you have them) using a #potato masher{}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place the @sausages{8} on a #baking tray{} (with some foil underneath to save washing up!). Cook the sausages under a hot #grill{} for ~{15%minutes}, turning occasionally to get a nice all over colour.

Once cooked, slice the sausages at an angle and serve with a mound of the potato and a big cowboy ladle of the smoked beans!